id: pm-yo3f
title: 2026-06-07 agent UX package ecosystem and path guardrail hardening
description: "Manual audit and implementation pass across pm CLI, pm SDK, agent-token output, external package ecosystem, GitHub reports, CI/CD, Sentry/telemetry, and temp-project dogfood. Duplicate check: searched broad audit SDK ecosystem agent UX external packages sentry telemetry github; only prior dated audit tasks were closed, no in-progress work existed, and GitHub issue #140 is the current actionable agent-UX report."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[6]: agent-ux,audit,ecosystem,github,observability,sdk
created_at: "2026-06-07T08:15:35.100Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T09:32:19.626Z"
author: codex-broad-ecosystem-audit-20260607
parent: pm-doxj
resolution: "Implemented --pm-path guardrails, completed ecosystem audit, and recorded verification/observability evidence."
expected_result: "Agents have safer tracker-path semantics, issue #140 is remediated, external packages and gates are verified, and tracker evidence is complete."
actual_result: "Added preferred --pm-path alias, workspace-root init guard with --force override, docs/completions/contracts/tests/changelog updates, 17-package smoke evidence, green linked tests/coverage/contracts/docs/security/Sentry gates, and closed/released pm-yo3f."
comments[9]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T08:16:00.000Z",codex-broad-ecosystem-audit-20260607,"Duplicate check evidence: pm context/list-in-progress found no active implementation work; pm search found prior broad audit tasks pm-z0ip/pm-kddw/pm-etxf as closed; open GitHub issue #140 is in scope for this fresh dated implementation task."
  "2026-06-07T08:19:36.823Z",codex-docs-agent-ux-review-20260607,"Sub-agent docs/agent-UX review: reviewed README.md, AGENTS.md, docs/COMMANDS.md, docs/CONFIGURATION.md, docs/TESTING.md, docs/EXTENSIONS.md, and docs/SDK.md for progressive disclosure, stale examples, duplicated guidance, token-efficient output guidance, and agent blockers. Finding: no blocking stale command examples or broken requested-doc links found; command-surface spot checks matched current help/contracts for install/package/upgrade/comments/docs/plan. Small fix applied: removed duplicated npm registry-404 fallback paragraph in docs/EXTENSIONS.md so package-source guidance appears once. Verification: pm test pm-yo3f --run --progress passed pnpm build and pnpm quality:docs-links."
  "2026-06-07T08:22:42.096Z",codex-sdk-review-20260607,"Sub-agent SDK review: reviewed src/sdk/index.ts, src/sdk/testing.ts, src/sdk/runtime.ts, src/sdk/package-runtime-options.ts, src/sdk/package-import-adapters.ts, src/core/packages/manifest.ts, docs/SDK.md, docs/EXTENSIONS.md, package scaffold/docs, and focused SDK/package tests. Findings: (1) Agent contract snapshot drift: pnpm contracts:check fails because live init contracts include --force but tests/fixtures/contracts/full.json is missing it at line 2619; stable temp diff shows only the added init --force flag. Recommended fix: run pnpm contracts:update, review fixture diff, and include intentional changelog/pm evidence. (2) Low-risk package-author ergonomics/docs-code mismatch: src/cli/commands/extension/scaffold.ts:47-58 says package mode emits documented defineExtension SDK shape, but lines 59-78 always emit the import-free JSDoc/plain object shape and tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts:224-227 explicitly assert no defineExtension import for package init. The scaffold works, but decide whether package init should be SDK-first defineExtension for richer package authoring or update the comment/docs to state package init intentionally stays dependency-light. Verification: npm install -g .; pm --version=2026.6.7; node v25.9.0; pnpm 10.33.4; pnpm build PASS; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/sdk-index.spec.ts tests/unit/package-manifest.spec.ts tests/unit/package-runtime-options.spec.ts tests/unit/package-import-adapters.spec.ts tests/integration/package-command-discovery.integration.spec.ts PASS (5 files, 73 tests); temp project /tmp/pm-sdk-review-xHSSbT init/package-init/install/invoke/doctor PASS; runtime contract for full command path agent-workflow-package ping PASS; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift ok with existing validate_resolution_missing_fields:89 warning; pnpm contracts:check FAIL as above. Changed files by this sub-agent: none."
  "2026-06-07T08:23:41.857Z",codex-github-observability-review-20260607,"Sub-agent GitHub/observability review: gh repo view confirmed unbraind/pm-cli public repo, admin viewer, default branch main. gh pr list found no open PRs. gh issue list found one open issue, #140 Clarify --path semantics for agents and add safe guardrails, which matches this work item. gh run list found latest main CI run 27087018491 on 9c77af88 failed; gh run view/log-failed isolated it to Gates static -> pnpm changelog:pm:check, with CHANGELOG.md out of date after latest tracker close/release state. Local pnpm changelog:pm:check reproduced the same failure. CodeQL latest main run 27087018500 succeeded; latest Nightly Validation 27086714005 succeeded. Security checks: gh vulnerability-alerts endpoint returned 204 enabled; dependabot/code-scanning/secret-scanning alert list endpoints returned 404 via gh API, so not usable as clean/dirty evidence. pnpm audit --audit-level moderate passed with no known vulnerabilities. pnpm security:scan passed with no credential-like secrets detected in tracked files. Observability: sentry-telemetry-gate passed in best-effort mode with live SENTRY_PERSONAL_ADMIN_TOKEN, critical=0, high=0, ignored_expected_cli_error_total=14, telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=2.07, missing error-code rows=0. scripts/prod/telemetry/check-stack-health.sh showed remote stack healthy, API version 2026.6.7, RabbitMQ pm.telemetry.events queue depth 0 consumers 1, Postgres 17099 events in last 24h. Workflow review: CI uses pinned actions, least contents:read permission, concurrency cancellation, full-history checkout for changelog/static gates; CodeQL has security-events:write; Dependabot weekly npm and GitHub Actions groups are configured. Local release-gate subset node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --json --skip-dogfood --skip-compatibility --telemetry-mode best-effort ... failed at coverage because concurrent --path/--pm-path lane edits currently break tests/unit/bootstrap-args.spec.ts and tests/unit/completion-command.spec.ts; did not patch because this overlaps active implementation lane rather than a disjoint CI/docs fix. Changed files by this sub-agent: none; reverted incidental pm-changelog managed-extension timestamp side effect."
  "2026-06-07T08:42:15.350Z",codex-external-package-smoke-20260607,"Sub-agent external package smoke: bootstrap and current external package smoke complete.\n\nCommands/results:\n- `npm install -g .` -> ok, up to date.\n- `pm --version` -> 2026.6.7; `node -v` -> v25.9.0; `pnpm -v` -> 10.33.4.\n- `pnpm build` -> passed.\n- `pnpm smoke:external-packages -- --discover-only --limit 25` -> ok=true, discovered 17 packages: pm-changelog, pm-jira, pm-github, pm-csv, @unbrained/pm-web, pm-beads, pm-graph, pm-gantt-chart, pm-slack, pm-slack-standup, pm-todos, pm-linear, pm-ts-starter, pm-presets, pm-starter, pm-brief, pm-context.\n- `npm view pm-changelog version dist-tags --json` -> latest 2026.6.7.\n- `pnpm smoke:external-packages -- --limit 25 --timeout-ms 180000` -> ok=true, cli_version=2026.6.7, tested=17, failed=0. Each package installed into an isolated temp project and passed init, install, `package doctor --project --detail deep --trace`, and `contracts --runtime-only --availability-only` with activation_failure_count=0 and blocking_failure_count=0.\n- Non-blocking doctor warnings from the successful full run: pm-todos reported `extension_command_handler_collision`; pm-ts-starter and pm-starter reported `extension_output_renderer_override_global` and `extension_output_service_override_global`. These did not block activation or runtime contracts.\n- Project-local `node dist/cli.js package doctor --project --detail summary --json` -> status ok, warning_count=0, activation_failure_count=0, blocking_failure_count=0, active_total=1 for managed pm-changelog.\n- Project-local `node dist/cli.js contracts --runtime-only --availability-only --json` -> `changelog-export` and `changelog-generate` are invocable extension actions from provider=extension.\n\nCaveat: a duplicate focused rerun of pm-todos, pm-ts-starter, and pm-starter later timed out during installs after 180s each while other smoke/changelog npm install processes were active. Because the prior full discovered smoke had already passed those packages and active concurrent npm/package processes were visible, I am treating that rerun as environmental install contention evidence, not a package compatibility failure.\n\nChanged files: none by this sub-agent. Source/doc changes currently visible in git status are from other lanes.\n"
  "2026-06-07T08:53:04.117Z",codex-broad-ecosystem-audit-20260607,"Evidence: direct real-repo changelog check passed: node dist/cli.js changelog generate --output CHANGELOG.md --title 'Changelog' --mode replace --all-release-tags --status closed --item-url-base https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/blob/main/.agents/pm --check reported action=unchanged changed=false item_count=1016. Removed it from linked tests because linked tracker-context copies tracker data into a temp PM_PATH while writing to real CHANGELOG.md, making the comparison invalid."
  "2026-06-07T08:57:43.712Z",codex-broad-ecosystem-audit-20260607,"Evidence: final local gates passed: linked pm test run passed 5/5; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 147 files / 2545 tests with 100% reported coverage; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift ok with existing validate_resolution_missing_fields:89 warning and no history drift; pm health --check-only --summary ok with telemetry_queue_pending:111 warning; sentry-telemetry-gate best-effort passed critical=0 high=0 telemetry_error_rate_pct=2.07 missing_error_code_rows=0; direct changelog --check passed changed=false item_count=1016; pnpm security:scan passed. npm audit retries in this lane hit npm registry ETIMEDOUT, while GitHub/observability sub-agent recorded an earlier successful pnpm audit with no known vulnerabilities."
  "2026-06-07T09:16:03.296Z",codex-broad-ecosystem-audit-20260607,"Evidence: post-PR CI static failure fixed by moving the workspace-root --pm-path regression into tests/integration/init-path-guard.integration.spec.ts and keeping tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts below the static line threshold. Fresh gates after the move: pnpm quality:static passed; focused regression slice passed 4 files/219 tests; linked pm test passed 7/7 including Sentry/telemetry, coverage 148 files/2545 tests, build, contracts, docs links, and security scan; pm validate showed no history drift and only the known legacy resolution metadata warning."
  "2026-06-07T09:32:19.626Z",codex-broad-ecosystem-audit-20260607,"Review follow-up: addressed valid CodeRabbit findings by making bootstrap --pm-path precedence match runtime resolution, stripping pmPath from command-scoped mutation options, adding init.force to the action schema contract plus generated snapshot, and adding fish --pm-path completion coverage. Kept CHANGELOG.md package-owned; direct changelog --check remains unchanged/current, so the generated Unreleased entry was not hand-edited. Evidence: focused tests passed 5 files/240 tests; pnpm quality:static passed; pnpm contracts:check passed after pnpm contracts:update; linked pm test passed 7/7 with Sentry/telemetry, coverage 148 files/2547 tests, focused tests, build, contracts, docs links, and security scan."
